# Always Use Existing Components Rule

## Critical Component Usage Guidelines

### NEVER Create Custom Components When Existing Ones Exist
- **ALWAYS check existing components first** before creating new ones
- **ALWAYS use `AppOTP`** for OTP inputs instead of custom HTML inputs
- **ALWAYS use `AppText`** for all text/typography instead of native HTML elements
- **ALWAYS use shadcn/ui components** for buttons, forms, and UI elements

### Component Reference List

#### Form Components
- [AppOTP.tsx](mdc:src/Pages/AuthPages/components/OTPLogin/AppOTP.tsx) - Use for OTP inputs (Better to access it via AppForm)
- [AppForm.tsx](mdc:src/components/Commmon/AppForm/AppForm.tsx) - Use for all forms
- [AppInput.tsx](mdc:src/components/Commmon/AppForm/AppInput.tsx) - Use for text inputs
- [AppSelect.tsx](mdc:src/components/Commmon/AppForm/AppSelect.tsx) - Use for dropdowns

#### UI Components
- [AppText.tsx](mdc:src/components/Commmon/AppText.tsx) - Use for ALL text/typography
- [Button.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx) - Use for all buttons
- [AppTable.tsx](mdc:src/components/Commmon/AppTable/AppTable.tsx) - Use for data tables

#### Layout Components
- [AppLayout.tsx](mdc:src/components/layout/MainLayout/AppLayout.tsx) - Use for page layouts
- [AppPageWrapper.tsx](mdc:src/components/Commmon/AppPageWrapper.tsx) - Use for page containers

### Examples of Correct Usage

#### ✅ CORRECT - Using Existing Components
```typescript
import AppOTP from "./AppOTP";
import AppText from "@/components/Commmon/AppText";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";


// Text Elements
<AppText type="h1" className="text-2xl font-bold">Title</AppText>
<AppText type="p" className="text-gray-600">Description</AppText>

// Buttons
<Button variant="default">Click Me</Button>
```

#### ❌ INCORRECT - Creating Custom Components
```typescript
// DON'T create custom OTP inputs
<div className="flex gap-4">
  {[0,1,2,3].map(index => (
    <input key={index} type="text" maxLength={1} />
  ))}
</div>

// DON'T use native HTML elements for text
<h1>Title</h1>
<p>Description</p>

// DON'T create custom buttons
<button className="custom-button">Click Me</button>
```

### Before Creating Any New Component
1. **Search existing components** in `src/components/Commmon/`
2. **Check shadcn/ui components** in `src/components/ui/`
3. **Look for similar functionality** in existing codebase
4. **Ask if existing component can be extended** instead of creating new one

### File Locations to Check First
- `src/components/Commmon/` - Custom reusable components
- `src/components/ui/` - shadcn/ui components
- `src/components/layout/` - Layout components
- `src/Pages/ProtectedPaths/` - Existing page patterns

### Benefits of Using Existing Components
- **Consistency**: Maintains design system consistency
- **Maintainability**: Easier to maintain and update
- **Accessibility**: Existing components have accessibility built-in
- **Performance**: Optimized and tested components
- **Development Speed**: Faster development with proven components

This rule ensures the codebase remains maintainable and consistent while leveraging the existing component library.